messages.message:
Patch Set 3:

Ah, the problem is raised from using intent lock for mkdir:
https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/36924/21/lustre/llite/namei.c

ll_mkdir()
        rc = ll_d_init(dchild);
	if (rc)
		GOTO(out_fini, rc);

	d_add(dchild, inode);

i.e.
stat /mnt/lustre/dir # 'dir' is a not existed directory.
mkdir /mnt/lustre/dir

during stat(), the dentry for 'dir' is valid cached in dcache.
then at the time of mkdir, d_add will call d_rehash, it will fail...

I think it could be fixed roughly in the WBC patch:
if (d_unhashed(dchild)) {
        rc = ll_d_init(dchild);
	if (rc)
		GOTO(out_fini, rc);

	d_add(dchild, inode);
} else {
       d_instantiate(dchild, inode);
}
